This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing. Additionally, the use of a Kaldi TDNN network suggests a focus on machine learning techniques for speech recognition. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech and accents. 

cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with processing speech signals. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possibility as the paper proposes a domain adversarial training algorithm to improve the performance of the speech recognition model. 

Finally, cs.SD (Systems and Control) could be a relevant sub-category as the paper deals with improving the performance of a speech recognition system.
